Reasoning: The paper presents adaptive and distributed algorithms for motion coordination of a group of vehicles in a stochastic and dynamic environment. This involves optimization and control of a multi-agent system, which falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The use of algorithms for motion coordination suggests that the paper may also fall under Robotics (cs.RO). The stochastic and dynamic nature of the environment suggests that the paper may involve Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for decision-making and learning. The use of control policies and performance guarantees suggests that the paper may also fall under Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of optimization techniques and performance guarantees suggests that the paper may also fall under Machine Learning (cs.LG).
